reviews.text:
This review is for the cafe.
It is right by the beach, great views, spacious, wide selection of drinks with some great options.
Quick service, friendly staff, speaking English.
Tiger prawns, glass of beer after paddling in the South China Sea. Well worth the cheap ferry over to the island and the walk up to the lookout past the beach

Worst  terrace restaurant ever. We ordered a Submarine sandwich, a Concerto club sandwich and a dish of spring rolls.. First Submarine sandwich comes with a piece of “STONED” baguette... hardly chewable and they don’t put any sauce to moisturize a bit.. worst. And the Fries, they were not freshly fried.. must have stayed long time in the kitchen. Spring rolls were not good as well.  A pint of Tsingtao was very watery. Do not recommend... but the terrace and view is nice.

Have not been to the hotel above but this bar / restaurant is right by the beach walk. Grab a table overlooking the sea and enjoy a long neck beer, free WiFi and some comfortable settees. Western food served here. Despite the power station next door, this beach is very quiet and safe. Restrooms and shower available by the life saver office

At the weekend if sunny day the beach is full of people in summer time. Night time is a peaceful moment to relax. Recommend to stay over and enjoy the quiet moment on the beach. If you come at weekday it will be less crowd.

reviews.text:
The best beach on the island but unfortunately the power station view sort of kills it for me, even though it is a bit further away from the  station than the neighbouring bigger beach.
Beach is sandy with a mixture of rocks spread out along its length.
Good for chilling or enjoying a drink in the nearby cafes.
Clean beach, clean water, lifeguard, cafe good for beers (we didn't eat). The power station is visible
Nice beach with barbecues areas for all, and clean facilities ! Ideal for families and groups of friends to hang. But really too close to the power station and its pollution!

Great little beach twenty to thirty minutes out from Yung Shue Wan main street.

Could do with showers in changing area but does have some showers outside.
Nice place for tourists in Hong Kong.. it is small but nice beach in lama island.. take ferry from central ferry pier towards lama island and reach there and explore the place..
漂亮的海灘，十分安靜悠閒～

reviews.text: Easy to access from the main island via ferry. Recommend getting to the beach by 10a.m. on the weekend. It fills up fast with families. Water is perfect temp and plenty of restaurants near by. About a 25 min walk from the pier.
Enjoyed my weekend escape here. Nice walk from Pier. Small beach. Not sure about water quality as it is so close to power plant

Six years ago this island and beach were my favorite! Lots of trees and nearly white sand mixed with rocks, nice lifeguards and warm, clear water. 

It's so sad to see what happend. It's so dirty in the water now and there is an unbelievable amount of rubbish all over the shore! Also big parts of the island are covered with it. Most of it are plastics so they will not decompose. 

Shower facilities are clean and the nice lifeguards are still there and doing their job well.
Enjoy my free time there.
風景優美，熱鬧非凡，人人開心，就是快樂。

四月份仍稍涼，未能下水，但水很清，不錯。
沙灘水質一般，垃圾多
